  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "ESD Engineer",
  "description": "<p>Job Description</p><p><strong>Role and Responsibilities: </strong></p><ul><li><p>To be part of a team of ESD architects/engineers to work on Environmental Sustainable Design (ESD)/ Green Mark /Green Building Index (GBI)/ LEED/ WELL projects</p></li><li><p>To manage projects related to overall sustainability, decarbonization and carbon advisory</p></li><li><p>To provide high level energy analysis and benchmarking energy consumption against best practices guideline and net zero roadmap for master planning in Singapore and overseas </p></li><li><p>To provide cost-effective solution to project teams for improving building performance, decarbonization and sustainability </p></li><li><p>To research on, review, recommend and implement industry best practices in sustainable building design and system </p></li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Qualifications</strong></p><ul><li><p>Bachelor’s or Master’s degree in M&E, Architecture, building serves, building sustainability or a related field</p></li><li><p>Minimum of 3 years of professional ESD experience in ESD</p></li><li><p>Process a strong knowledge on common energy analysis/benchmarking, Excel-based energy calculation and energy modeling software, with a specific focus on IESVE or EnergyPlus</p></li><li><p>Good understanding of building system, particularly in ACMV system and other M&E disciplines</p></li><li><p>GMAP, LEED AP, WELL AP or credentials in related areas will be considered an advantage, as will the ASHRAE BEMP certificate (building energy modeling professional)</p></li><li><p>Experience with modeling support software such as Open Studio and Rhino is desirable</p></li><li><p>Project management skills with ability to actively manage and balance task, cost and time</p></li><li><p>Team player with the ability to work as a team, willing to learn, contribute ideas and assist team member with tasks/duties, when required</p></li><li><p>Highly self-driven and pro-active with a keen interest for exploring innovative solutions</p></li><li><p>Broad based experience of computer systems and MS Office applications</p></li></ul>",
